<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-391-560  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 391 560.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  June 1990 v7 n6 p237(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Know your Stuff 2.1. (an easy-to-use personal and businessinventory system) (Software Review) (Window Shopping) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Stevens, Lawrence.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Working Systems' $49.95 Know Your Stuff is an application based onthe Omnis-3 database designed for inventorying personalpossessions.andP;  It can be customized for almost any list type, andit is convenient for both personal and small business use.andP;  Theuser first chooses the general categories of items to track andthen designates each as single or multiple.andP;  Eight preset 'Label'fields in each category include Name, Type, Date, Unit Cost,Location, Description, Last Modified Date, and Time.andP;  Categoriesdesignates as 'multiple' add Quantity, Total Cost, Max Quantity,and Min Quantity fields.andP;  Users can prepare reports with a manylogical comparisons.andP;  The documentation is inadequate, and oneserious deficiency is the lack of support for address labels.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Working Systems (products).andO;Product:   Know Your Stuff 2.1 (Computer program).andO;Topic:     Software packagesEvaluationInventory Control.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>